      "writtenOn": "2020-11-05T21:36:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We have some macros for the luminance coefficients.  Looking at the spec, the matrix terms have one of two forms:\n\n K + (1-K)s \u003d\u003d K(1-s) + s\n\n or\n\n K(1-s)\n\nI think this could all be written as\n  const auto lr \u003d SK_LUM_COEFF_R * (1 - s),\n             lg \u003d SK_LUM_COEFF_G * (1 - s),\n             lb \u003d SK_LUM_COEFF_B * (1 - s);\n\n\n  return SkColorMatrix(\n      lr + s, lg    , lb    , 0, 0,\n      lr    , lg + s, lb    , 0, 0,\n      lr    , lg    , lb + s, 0, 0,\n      0     , 0     ,      0, 1, 0\n  );",
      "revId": "bebae4723acc0bc030f2e05c52629702511f9a58",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
